Review dimension: UI/UX
Severity: medium
File: src/app/dom-builders.ts:209-218
Title: Open menu is not dismissed on scroll or viewport resize

Finding:
The dropdown is position:fixed at viewport coords and its open state registers only document 'click' and 'keydown' (Escape) listeners. If the user scrolls the .results container (overflow:auto) or the page, or resizes the window while the menu is open, the menu stays pinned at its original viewport position, now detached from the row that owns it — confusing and potentially pointing at the wrong row's data. Standard dropdowns close (or re-anchor) on scroll/resize.

Fix instructions (follow exactly; make targeted, minimal changes):
In src/app/dom-builders.ts makeRowMenu, dismiss the menu on scroll and resize while it is open. In openMenu, after registering the existing document 'click' and 'keydown' listeners, also register a listener that closes the menu on any scroll (capturing, so it catches scrolls inside the .results overflow container as well as window scroll) and on window resize. E.g. add named handlers:

function onScrollOrResize(): void { closeMenu(); }
window.addEventListener('scroll', onScrollOrResize, true);
window.addEventListener('resize', onScrollOrResize);

and in closeMenu remove them with the same arguments (useCapture=true for scroll):

window.removeEventListener('scroll', onScrollOrResize, true);
window.removeEventListener('resize', onScrollOrResize);

Keep the existing click/Escape behavior and listener teardown unchanged.

